page_analysis.text_content:
Attached garages/carports site planning

• Attached garages must comply with same setbacks as main dwelling.

Note: Uncovered spaces must be located beyond the required frontyard and beyond the first 10' of the street-side yard.

Fig 33 Examples of site planning solutions for attached garages/carports

A 1-car garage with 2nd space (uncovered) located in the sideyard

B 1-car garage with 2nd space (uncovered) located in the driveway

C 2-car garage with no uncovered spaces

visual_elements.description: Three side-by-side site planning diagrams labeled A, B, and C illustrating examples of attached garages/carports on different lot types. Each diagram shows a lot with labeled areas: 'Buildable area' in light gray, 'Main dwelling' in medium gray, and attached garages in black labeled '1-car attached' or '2-car attached'. The diagrams include lot lines, sidewalks, curbs, required setbacks (dashed lines), no-parking areas (hatched lines), and uncovered spaces (depicted with a car icon). The first two diagrams (A and B) are interior lot examples with rear yards and front yards, while the third (C) is a corner lot example. A 10-foot measurement is shown on the street-side yard in the corner lot example. The diagrams visually differentiate between uncovered spaces located in the sideyard or driveway and no uncovered spaces.
A gray shaded box containing a note: 'Note: Uncovered spaces must be located beyond the required frontyard and beyond the first 10' of the street-side yard.'
